==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic: cognate with Old Saxon [[thunkian]] (Dutch [[dunken]]), Old High German [[thunken]] (German [[dünken]]), Old Norse [[þykkja]] (Swedish [[tycka]]), Gothic [[𐌸𐌿𐌲𐌺𐌾𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'θynʧan/

===Verb===
'''þynċan''' (weak verb class 1: '''þynċe''' ‘it seems’; '''þūhte''' ‘it seemed’; '''þūhton''' ‘they seemed’; '''ġeþūht''' past participle)
# to [[seem]], [[appear]]

